README for developers and network ops

(readme for end users is in docs/readme.txt)

If you are starting a new network, you need to edit dtella/network.cfg
before you do the build.

== Windows / Mac OS X ==

Instructions in docs/requirements.txt

== setup.py ==

This accepts the standard python install targets; see setup.py --help for more
details.

Extra stuff:

Specifying --bridge as a general (as opposed to target) option will include the
bridge modules in the build

Additionally, there is a bdist_shinst target which will build a shell script to
install dtella and its dependencies from a remote source build.
